If we can have a crn in the response but not stackresponse, it means that the response could have other useful info in it. So I think a better solution would be to handle the possible NPE in the hasSpotTermination assignment, something like this:
boolean hasSpotTermination = Optional.ofNullable(getResponse().getStackV4Response()) .map(stack -> stack.getInstanceGroups()) .stream() .flatMap(ig -> ig.getMetadata().stream()) .anyMatch(metadata -> InstanceStatus.DELETED_BY_PROVIDER == metadata.getInstanceStatus());
This way we could add the response to the report without an NPE. Also it is possible that other Investigables have this issue, please check them too.

